definition: to set/to fix/to determine/to decide/to order

sentences.english: You may be accountable to complete projects to deadline and under budget.
sentences.chinese: 你可能要負責在期限之內以既定的預算完成各項任務。

sentences.english: Maintain Health Club facilities accding to set stards of der cleanliness.
sentences.chinese: 按照既定次序和清潔標準來維護健身俱樂部設施。

sentences.english: To retrofit an established mold would be almost impossible.
sentences.chinese: 加裝一個既定的模具就幾乎是不可能的。

sentences.english: Some defined set of criteria determines where a router sends the message.
sentences.chinese: 某些既定的標準決定路由器將把信息發送到哪裏。

sentences.english: Is there a defined strategy for the sunset of legacy applications or functions?
sentences.chinese: 是否存在針對遺留應用程序或功能子集的既定策略？

sentences.english: This is a consistent guideline of Albania and will never change.
sentences.chinese: 這是阿的既定方針，不會改變。

sentences.english: Don’t just be a follower who adapts his or her self to the conditions that already exist.
sentences.chinese: 不要只做一個跟風者去適應業已既定的環境。

sentences.english: Do you worry about implementation of this declared policy?
sentences.chinese: 你擔心這項既定政策的實施嗎？

sentences.english: They laid the sails aback so as to stay on course in the storm wind.
sentences.chinese: 他們使帆成爲逆風向以便在暴風中保持既定航道。

sentences.english: The Austrian took more than two hours to get up to the jump altitude.
sentences.chinese: 鮑姆加特納花費了兩個多小時才升到既定高度。

sentences.english: Railway ballast will be loaded onto ballast trains at an established ballast siding.
sentences.chinese: 鐵路道碴，將載入碴列車在一個既定的鎮流器偏袒。

sentences.english: His knee locked towards the end of training and he could not complete the session.
sentences.chinese: 他的膝傷使他沒有能夠完成既定的訓練科目。

sentences.english: They laid the sails aback to stay on course in that wind.
sentences.chinese: 他們在吹這種風的情況下，換成逆帆來保持既定航線。

sentences.english: We will cut the buck and insist on advancing along our set goal.
sentences.chinese: 我們將不負重望，堅持不移按着既定目標，走下去。

sentences.english: As such, I delete questions that do not fall within the set guidelines of this thread.
sentences.chinese: 因此，我刪除問題，不屬於該線程的既定方針。

sentences.english: This recorded the voltage that each model made over a period of time.
sentences.chinese: 這個儀器記錄每一個模型在既定時間段產生的電壓。

definition: to follow the prescribed order; to keep to the working routine (idiom)
to comply with/to follow (directives)/to defer (to the judgment of superiors)
according to/in accordance with/in the light of/on the basis of
nothing much changes (idiom); always the same/stuck in a rut
to follow the compass and go with the set square (idiom); to follow the rules inflexibly/to act according to convention
to follow/to abide by/to comply with/compliance
fixed framework (idiom); restriction of social conventions and taboos (usually derogatory)/regulations and restrictions
